Top Stories (March 2)

BUSH SAYS ENERGY SECURITY TO BE HIS PRIORITY
U.S. President George W. Bush said Friday that he will make energy security 
"a priority of American foreign policy." It requires "restoring American 
credibility with overseas suppliers and building strong relationships with 
energy-producing nations in our hemisphere," he said at a swearing-in 
ceremony for his Energy Secretary Spencer Abraham.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/03/02/xh/0000-5054-us-energy

PACIFIC GAS & ELECTRIC AGREES TO SELL POWER LINES TO CALIFORNIA, SOURCES SAY
Marking a potential turning point in California's energy crisis, Pacific Gas 
and Electric has agreed to sell its transmission lines to the state as part 
of a larger deal to rescue the company from financial collapse, according to 
sources familiar with the negotiations.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/03/03/krtbn/0000-0314-SJ-POWER-DEAL

SOUTHERN COMPANY TO SPIN OFF MIRANT APRIL 2 AFTER IRS RULING
Southern Co. will spin off 80.3% of Mirant Corp.'s shares on April 2, to 
Southern Co. holders of record March 21. In a press release Friday, Southern 
Co. said it received a favorable Internal Revenue Service ruling concerning 
the tax-free distribution of 272 million Mirant shares.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
03/02/eng-djn/eng-djn_140056_174_71534114331

MIDWEST ISO: 8 UTILITIES JOINED GRID OPERATOR BEFORE WEDNESDAY DEADLINE
The Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator Inc. said Friday that 
eight utilities submitted conditional applications this week to join the 
planned power grid operating group.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
03/02/eng-djn/eng-djn_140057_171_893130457029

US FTC SEEKS INPUT FOR REPORT ON STATE RETAIL POWER PLANS
The U.S. Federal Trade Commission is seeking public comment for a report 
requested by House lawmakers assessing what state-sponsored retail power 
competition programs have truly produced consumer benefits.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
03/02/eng-djn/eng-djn_150105_35_1540475850925

LOS ANGELES DEPARTMENT OF WATER AND POWER TO SELL $1.2B IN POWER BONDS AS OF 
DEBT-RESTRUCTURING PLAN
The Los Angeles Department of Water and Power this week is selling $1.2 
billion in power bonds to refund fixed-rate electric system debt as part of 
an overall plan to restructure debt service.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/ambanker
/2001/03/02/news/0000-0056-KEYWORD.Missing

